Reasoning: The paper focuses on the communication performance of multi-connectivity in fifth-generation mobile networks, which falls under the domain of networked systems and communication technologies. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves the analysis of outage probability and throughput, which are related to information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with wireless communication systems, which falls under the domain of cs.COMM (Communications and Networking). The paper also involves the comparison of different combining algorithms, which falls under the domain of control and systems engineering, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper applies the analytical framework to real field channel measurements, which involves the processing and analysis of multimedia data, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible sub-category as well.
